http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Auxiliary-bishop-for-Kanjirappally/article13996082.ece

The Synod of bishops of the Syro-Malabar Church assembled at Mount St. Thomas, Kakkanad, has elected Jose Pulickal as the first auxiliary bishop of the Syro-Malabar Eparchy of Kanjirapally. The announcement of the election was made public at 12 noon (Italian time, 4.30 p. m. Indian time) on Tuesday, said a press release here.The Major Archbishop of the Syro-Malabar Church Cardinal George Alencherry made the announcement at Mount St. Thomas. The Major Archbishop and Bishop Mathew Arackal, Bishop of Kanjirapally presented the bishop-elect with the insignia of Episcopacy.Archbishop Joseph Powathil, first Bishop of Kanjirapally felicitated the bishop-elect presenting him with a bouquet.All the bishops attending the Synod of the Syro-Malabar Church were present at the occasion, the press release added.Syro-Malabar Church Archbishop Cardinal George Alencherry makes the announcement